# Replace this file with `site/CNAME` (no extension) to enable a custom
# domain. The CNAME file must contain exactly one line: the bare domain name.
# Example:
#
#   talos.example.com
#
# GitHub Pages reads `site/CNAME` automatically when Pages is configured to
# serve from the `site/` directory. Until a domain is selected, leave this
# file as `site/CNAME.example` so the repository does not pin an unowned
# domain.
#
# Reference: https://docs.github.com/en/pages/configuring-a-custom-domain-for-your-github-pages-site
